quran[169]{c,v,t}:
  33,31,"And whoever of you devoutly obeys Allah and His Messenger and does good, We will grant her double the reward, and We have prepared for her an honourable provision"
  33,32,"O wives of the Prophet! You are not like any other women: if you are mindful ňĻof Allahňļ, then do not be overly effeminate in speech ňĻwith menňļ or those with sickness in their hearts may be tempted, but speak in a moderate tone"
  33,33,"Settle in your homes, and do not display yourselves as women did in the days of ňĻpre-Islamicňļ ignorance. Establish prayer, pay alms-tax, and obey Allah and His Messenger. Allah only intends to keep ňĻthe causes ofňļ evil away from you and purify you completely, O members of the ňĻProphet‚Äôsňļ family"
  33,34,"ňĻAlwaysňļ remember what is recited in your homes of Allah‚Äôs revelations and ňĻpropheticňļ wisdom.¬†Surely Allah is Most Subtle, All-Aware"
  33,35,"Surely ňĻforňļ Muslim men and women, believing men and women,¬†devout men and women, truthful men and women, patient men and women, humble men and women, charitable men and women, fasting men and women, men and women who guard their chastity, and men and women who remember Allah often‚ÄĒfor ňĻall ofňļ them Allah has prepared forgiveness and a great reward"
  33,36,"It is not for a believing man or woman‚ÄĒwhen Allah and His Messenger decree a matter‚ÄĒto have any other choice in that matter.¬†Indeed, whoever disobeys Allah and His Messenger has clearly gone ňĻfarňļ astray"
  33,37,"And ňĻremember, O Prophet,ňļ when you said to the one¬†for whom Allah has done a favour and you ňĻtooňļ have done a favour,¬†‚ÄúKeep your wife and fear Allah,‚ÄĚ while concealing within yourself what Allah was going to reveal. And ňĻsoňļ you were considering the people, whereas Allah was more worthy of your consideration. So when Zaid totally lost interest in ňĻkeepingňļ his wife, We gave her to you in marriage, so that there would be no blame on the believers for marrying the ex-wives of their adopted sons after their divorce. And Allah‚Äôs command is totally binding"
  33,38,There is no blame on the Prophet for doing what Allah has ordained for him. That has been the way of Allah with those ňĻprophetsňļ who had gone before. And Allah‚Äôs command has been firmly decreed
  33,39,"ňĻThat is His way withňļ those ňĻprophetsňļ who deliver the messages of Allah, and consider Him, and none but Allah. And sufficient is Allah as a ňĻvigilantňļ Reckoner"
  33,40,"MuŠł•ammad is not the father of any of your men,¬†but is the Messenger of Allah and the seal of the prophets. And Allah has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  33,41,O believers! Always remember Allah often
  33,42,and glorify Him morning and evening
  33,43,He is the One Who showers His blessings upon you‚ÄĒand His angels pray for you‚ÄĒso that He may bring you out of darkness and into light. For He is ever Merciful to the believers
  33,44,"Their greeting on the Day they meet Him will be, ‚ÄúPeace!‚ÄĚ And He has prepared for them an honourable reward"
  33,45,"O Prophet! We have sent you as a witness, and a deliverer of good news, and a warner"
  33,46,"and a caller to ňĻthe Way ofňļ Allah by His command, and a beacon of light"
  33,47,Give good news to the believers that they will have a great bounty from Allah
  33,48,"Do not yield to the disbelievers and the hypocrites. Overlook their annoyances, and put your trust in Allah. For Allah is sufficient as a Trustee of Affairs"
  33,49,"O believers! If you marry believing women and then divorce them before you touch them,¬†they will have no waiting period for you to count,¬†so give them a ňĻsuitableňļ compensation, and let them go graciously"
  33,50,"O Prophet! We have made lawful for you your wives to whom you have paid their ňĻfullňļ dowries as well as those ňĻbondwomenňļ in your possession, whom Allah has granted you.¬†And ňĻyou are allowed to marryňļ the daughters of your paternal uncles and aunts, and the daughters of your maternal uncles and aunts, who have emigrated like you. Also ňĻallowed for marriage isňļ a believing woman who offers herself to the Prophet ňĻwithout dowryňļ if he is interested in marrying her‚ÄĒňĻthis isňļ exclusively for you, not for the rest of the believers.¬†We know well what ňĻrulingsňļ We have ordained for the believers in relation to their wives and those ňĻbondwomenňļ in their possession. As such, there would be no blame on you. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  33,51,"It is up to you ňĻO Prophetňļ to delay or receive whoever you please of your wives. There is no blame on you if you call back any of those you have set aside.¬†That is more likely that they will be content, not grieved, and satisfied with what you offer them all. Allah ňĻfullyňļ knows what is in your hearts. And Allah is All-Knowing, Most Forbearing"
  33,52,"It is not lawful for you ňĻO Prophetňļ to marry more women after this, nor can you replace any of your present wives with another, even if her beauty may attract you‚ÄĒexcept those ňĻbondwomenňļ in your possession. And Allah is ever Watchful over all things"
  33,53,"O believers! Do not enter the homes of the Prophet without permission ňĻand if invitedňļ for a meal, do not ňĻcome too early andňļ linger until the meal is ready. But if you are invited, then enter ňĻon timeňļ. Once you have eaten, then go on your way, and do not stay for casual talk. Such behaviour is truly annoying to the Prophet, yet he is too shy to ask you to leave. But Allah is never shy of the truth. And when you ňĻbelieversňļ ask his wives for something, ask them from behind a barrier. This is purer for your hearts and theirs. And it is not right for you to annoy the Messenger of Allah, nor ever marry his wives after him. This would certainly be a major offence in the sight of Allah"
  33,54,"Whether you reveal something or conceal it, surely Allah has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  33,55,"There is no blame on the Prophet‚Äôs wives ňĻif they appear unveiledňļ before their fathers,¬†their sons, their brothers, their brothers‚Äô sons, their sisters‚Äô sons, their fellow ňĻMuslimňļ women, and those ňĻbondspeopleňļ in their possession. And be mindful of Allah ňĻO wives of the Prophet!ňļ Surely Allah is a Witness over all things"
  33,56,"Indeed, Allah showers His blessings upon the Prophet, and His angels pray for him. O believers! Invoke Allah‚Äôs blessings upon him, and salute him with worthy greetings of peace"
  33,57,Surely those who offend Allah¬†and His Messenger¬†are condemned by Allah in this world and the Hereafter. And He has prepared for them a humiliating punishment
  33,58,"As for those who abuse believing men and women¬†unjustifiably, they will definitely bear the guilt of slander and blatant sin"
  33,59,"O Prophet! Ask your wives, daughters, and believing women to draw their cloaks over their bodies. In this way it is more likely that they will be recognized ňĻas virtuousňļ and not be harassed. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  33,60,"If the hypocrites, and those with sickness in their hearts, and rumour-mongers in Medina do not desist, We will certainly incite you ňĻO Prophetňļ against them, and then they will not be your neighbours there any longer"
  33,61,"ňĻThey deserve to beňļ condemned. ňĻIf they were to persist,ňļ they would get themselves seized and killed relentlessly wherever they are found"
  33,62,That was Allah‚Äôs way with those ňĻhypocritesňļ who have gone before. And you will find no change in Allah‚Äôs way
  33,63,"People ask you ňĻO Prophetňļ about the Hour. Say, ‚ÄúThat knowledge is only with Allah. You never know, perhaps the Hour is near.‚ÄĚ"
  33,64,"Surely Allah condemns the disbelievers, and has prepared for them a blazing Fire"
  33,65,to stay there for ever and ever‚ÄĒnever will they find any protector or helper
  33,66,"On the Day their faces are ňĻconstantlyňļ flipped in the Fire, they will cry, ‚ÄúOh! If only we had obeyed Allah and obeyed the Messenger!‚ÄĚ"
  33,67,"And they will say, ‚ÄúOur Lord! We obeyed our leaders and elite, but they led us astray from the ňĻRightňļ Way"
  33,68,"Our Lord! Give them double ňĻourňļ punishment, and condemn them tremendously.‚ÄĚ"
  33,69,"O believers! Do not be like those who slandered Moses, but Allah cleared him of what they said. And he was honourable in the sight of Allah"
  33,70,"O believers! Be mindful of Allah, and say what is right"
  33,71,"He will bless your deeds for you, and forgive your sins. And whoever obeys Allah and His Messenger, has truly achieved a great triumph"
  33,72,"Indeed, We offered the trust to the heavens and the earth and the mountains, but they ňĻallňļ declined to bear it, being fearful of it. But humanity assumed it, ňĻforňļ they are truly wrongful ňĻto themselvesňļ and ignorant ňĻof the consequencesňļ"
  33,73,"so that Allah will punish hypocrite men and women and polytheistic men and women, and Allah will turn in mercy to believing men and women. For Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  34,1,"All praise is for Allah, to Whom belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. And praise be to Him in the Hereafter. He is the All-Wise, All-Aware"
  34,2,"He knows whatever goes into the earth and whatever comes out of it, and whatever descends from the sky and whatever ascends into it. And He is the Most Merciful, All-Forgiving"
  34,3,"The disbelievers say, ‚ÄúThe Hour will never come to us.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúYes‚ÄĒby my Lord, the Knower of the unseen‚ÄĒit will certainly come to you!‚ÄĚ Not ňĻevenňļ an atom‚Äôs weight is hidden from Him in the heavens or the earth; nor anything smaller or larger than that, but is ňĻwrittenňļ in a perfect Record"
  34,4,So He may reward those who believe and do good. It is they who will have forgiveness and an honourable provision
  34,5,"As for those who strive to discredit Our revelations, it is they who will suffer the ňĻworstňļ torment of agonizing pain"
  34,6,"Those gifted with knowledge ňĻclearlyňļ see that what has been revealed to you from your Lord ňĻO Prophetňļ is the truth, and that it guides to the Path of the Almighty, the Praiseworthy"
  34,7,"The disbelievers say ňĻmockingly to one anotherňļ, ‚ÄúShall we show you a man who claims that when you have been utterly disintegrated you will be raised as a new creation"
  34,8,"Has he fabricated a lie against Allah or is he insane?‚ÄĚ In fact, those who do not believe in the Hereafter are bound for torment and have strayed farthest ňĻfrom the truthňļ"
  34,9,"Have they not then seen all that surrounds them of the heavens and the earth? If We willed, We could cause the earth to swallow them up, or cause ňĻdeadlyňļ pieces of the sky to fall upon them. Surely in this is a sign for every servant who turns ňĻto Allahňļ"
  34,10,"Indeed, We granted David a ňĻgreatňļ privilege from Us, ňĻcommanding:ňļ ‚ÄúO mountains! Echo his hymns! And the birds as well.‚ÄĚ We made iron mouldable for him"
  34,11,"instructing: ‚ÄúMake full-length armour, ňĻperfectlyňļ balancing the links. And work righteousness ňĻO family of David!ňļ. Indeed, I am All-Seeing of what you do.‚ÄĚ"
  34,12,"And to Solomon ňĻWe subjectedňļ the wind: its morning stride was a month‚Äôs journey and so was its evening stride. And We caused a stream of molten copper to flow for him, and ňĻWe subjectedňļ some of the jinn to work under him by his Lord‚Äôs Will. And whoever of them deviated from Our command, We made them taste the torment of the blaze"
  34,13,"They made for him whatever he desired of sanctuaries, statues,¬†basins as large as reservoirs, and cooking pots fixed ňĻinto the groundňļ. ňĻWe ordered:ňļ ‚ÄúWork gratefully, O family of David!‚ÄĚ ňĻOnlyňļ a few of My servants are ňĻtrulyňļ grateful"
  34,14,"When We decreed Solomon‚Äôs death, nothing indicated to the ňĻsubjectedňļ jinn that he was dead except the termites eating away his staff.¬†So when he collapsed, the jinn realized that if they had ňĻreallyňļ known the unseen, they would not have remained in ňĻsuchňļ humiliating servitude"
  34,15,"Indeed, there was a sign for ňĻthe tribe ofňļ Sheba in their homeland: two orchards‚ÄĒone to the right and the other to the left. ňĻThey were told:ňļ ‚ÄúEat from the provision of your Lord, and be grateful to Him. ňĻYours isňļ a good land and a forgiving Lord.‚ÄĚ"
  34,16,"But they turned away. So We sent against them a devastating flood, and replaced their orchards with two others producing bitter fruit, fruitless bushes,¬†and a few ňĻsparseňļ thorny trees"
  34,17,This is how We rewarded them for their ingratitude. Would We ever punish ňĻanyone in such a wayňļ except the ungrateful
  34,18,"We had also placed between them and the cities¬†We showered with blessings ňĻmany smallňļ towns within sight of one another. And We set moderate travel distances in between, ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúTravel between them by day and night safely.‚ÄĚ"
  34,19,"But they said, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Make ňĻthe distances ofňļ our journeys longer,‚ÄĚ wronging themselves.¬†So We reduced them to ňĻcautionaryňļ tales, and scattered them utterly. Surely in this are lessons for whoever is steadfast, grateful"
  34,20,"Indeed, Ibl√ģs‚Äô assumption about them has come true,¬†so they ňĻallňļ follow him, except a group of ňĻtrueňļ believers"
  34,21,"He does not have any authority over them, but ňĻOur Will isňļ only to distinguish those who believe in the Hereafter from those who are in doubt about it. And your Lord is a ňĻvigilantňļ Keeper over all things.‚ÄĚ"
  34,22,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúCall upon those you claim ňĻto be divineňļ besides Allah. They do not possess ňĻevenňļ an atom‚Äôs weight either in the heavens or the earth, nor do they have any share in ňĻgoverningňļ them. Nor is any of them a helper to Him.‚ÄĚ"
  34,23,"No intercession will be of any benefit with Him, except by those granted permission by Him. ňĻAt last,ňļ when the dread ňĻof Judgment Dayňļ is relieved from their hearts ňĻbecause they are permitted to intercedeňļ, they will ňĻexcitedlyňļ ask ňĻthe angelsňļ, ‚ÄúWhat has your Lord ňĻjustňļ said?‚ÄĚ The angels will reply, ‚ÄúThe truth! And He is the Most High, All-Great.‚ÄĚ"
  34,24,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúWho provides for you from the heavens and the earth?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúAllah! Now, certainly one of our two groups¬†is ňĻrightlyňļ guided; the other is clearly astray.‚ÄĚ"
  34,25,"Say, ‚ÄúYou will not be accountable for our misdeeds, nor will we be accountable for your deeds.‚ÄĚ"
  34,26,"Say, ‚ÄúOur Lord will gather us together, then He will judge between us with the truth. For He is the All-Knowing Judge.‚ÄĚ"
  34,27,"Say, ‚ÄúShow me those ňĻidolsňļ you have joined with Him as partners. No! In fact, He ňĻaloneňļ is Allah‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Wise.‚ÄĚ"
  34,28,"We have sent you ňĻO Prophetňļ only as a deliverer of good news and a warner to all of humanity, but most people do not know"
  34,29,"And they ask ňĻthe believersňļ, ‚ÄúWhen will this threat come to pass, if what you say is true?‚ÄĚ"
  34,30,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúA Day has ňĻalreadyňļ been appointed for you, which you can neither delay nor advance by a ňĻsingleňļ moment.‚ÄĚ"
  34,31,"The disbelievers vow, ‚ÄúWe will never believe in this Quran, nor in those ňĻScripturesňļ before it.‚ÄĚ If only you could see when the wrongdoers will be detained before their Lord, throwing blame at each other! The lowly ňĻfollowersňļ will say to the arrogant ňĻleadersňļ, ‚ÄúHad it not been for you, we would certainly have been believers.‚ÄĚ"
  34,32,"The arrogant will respond to the lowly, ‚ÄúDid we ever hinder you from guidance after it came to you? In fact, you were wicked ňĻon your ownňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  34,33,"The lowly will say to the arrogant, ‚ÄúNo! It was your plotting by day and night‚ÄĒwhen you ordered us to disbelieve in Allah and to set up equals with Him.‚ÄĚ They will ňĻallňļ hide ňĻtheirňļ remorse when they see the torment. And We will put shackles around the necks of the disbelievers. Will they be rewarded except for what they used to do"
  34,34,"Whenever We sent a warner to a society, its elite would say, ‚ÄúWe truly reject what you have been sent with.‚ÄĚ"
  34,35,"Adding, ‚ÄúWe are far superior ňĻto the believersňļ in wealth and children, and we will never be punished.‚ÄĚ"
  34,36,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúSurely ňĻit isňļ my Lord ňĻWhoňļ gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills. But most people do not know.‚ÄĚ"
  34,37,"It is not your wealth or children that bring you closer to Us. But those who believe and do good‚ÄĒit is they who will have a multiplied reward for what they did, and they will be secure in ňĻelevatedňļ mansions"
  34,38,"As for those who strive to discredit Our revelations, it is they who will be confined in punishment"
  34,39,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúSurely ňĻit isňļ my Lord ňĻWhoňļ gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills of His servants. And whatever you spend in charity, He will compensate ňĻyouňļ for it. For He is the Best Provider.‚ÄĚ"
  34,40,"And ňĻconsiderňļ the Day He will gather them all together, and then ask the angels, ‚ÄúWas it you that these ňĻpolytheistsňļ used to worship?‚ÄĚ"
  34,41,"They will say, ‚ÄúGlory be to You! Our loyalty is to You, not them. In fact, they ňĻonlyňļ followed the ňĻtemptations of evilňļ jinn,¬†in whom most of them had faith.‚ÄĚ"
  34,42,"So Today neither of you can benefit or protect each other. And We will say to the wrongdoers, ‚ÄúTaste the torment of the Fire, which you used to deny.‚ÄĚ"
  34,43,"When Our clear revelations are recited to them, they say, ‚ÄúThis is only a man who wishes to hinder you from what your forefathers used to worship.‚ÄĚ They also say, ‚ÄúThis ňĻQuranňļ is no more than a fabricated lie.‚ÄĚ And the disbelievers say of the truth when it has come to them, ‚ÄúThis is nothing but pure magic.‚ÄĚ"
  34,44,"ňĻThey say so even thoughňļ We had never given them any scriptures to study, nor did We ever send them a warner before you ňĻO Prophetňļ"
  34,45,"Those ňĻdestroyedňļ before them denied as well‚ÄĒand these ňĻMeccansňļ have not attained even one-tenth of what We had given their predecessors.¬†Yet ňĻwhenňļ they denied My messengers, how severe was My response"
  34,46,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI advise you to do ňĻonlyňļ one thing: stand up for ňĻthe sake ofňļ Allah‚ÄĒindividually or in pairs‚ÄĒthen reflect. Your fellow man¬†is not insane. He is only a warner to you before ňĻthe coming ofňļ a severe punishment.‚ÄĚ"
  34,47,"Say, ‚ÄúIf I had ever asked you for a reward, you could keep it. My reward is only from Allah. And He is a Witness over all things.‚ÄĚ"
  34,48,"Say, ‚ÄúSurely my Lord hurls the truth ňĻagainst falsehoodňļ. ňĻHe isňļ the Knower of all unseen.‚ÄĚ"
  34,49,"Say, ‚ÄúThe truth has come, and falsehood will vanish, never to return.‚ÄĚ"
  34,50,"Say, ‚ÄúIf I am astray, the loss is only mine. And if I am guided, it is ňĻonlyňļ because of what my Lord reveals to me. He is indeed All-Hearing, Ever Near.‚ÄĚ"
  34,51,If only you could see when they will be horrified with no escape ňĻon Judgment Dayňļ! And they will be seized from a nearby place
  34,52,"They will ňĻthenňļ cry, ‚ÄúWe do ňĻnowňļ believe in it ňĻallňļ.‚ÄĚ But how could they ňĻpossiblyňļ attain faith from a place so far-off ňĻfrom the worldňļ"
  34,53,"while they had already rejected it before, guessing blindly from a place ňĻequallyňļ far-away ňĻfrom the Hereafterňļ"
  34,54,"They will be sealed off from whatever they desire, as was done to their counterparts before. Indeed, they were ňĻallňļ in alarming doubt"
  35,1,"All praise is for Allah, the Originator of the heavens and the earth, Who made angels ňĻas Hisňļ messengers with wings‚ÄĒtwo, three, or four. He increases in creation whatever He wills. Surely Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  35,2,"Whatever mercy Allah opens up for people, none can withhold it. And whatever He withholds, none but Him can release it. For He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  35,3,O humanity! Remember Allah‚Äôs favours upon you. Is there any creator other than Allah who provides for you from the heavens and the earth? There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. How can you then be deluded ňĻfrom the truthňļ
  35,4,"If you are rejected by them, so too were messengers before you. And to Allah ňĻallňļ matters will be returned ňĻfor judgmentňļ"
  35,5,"O humanity! Indeed, Allah‚Äôs promise is true. So do not let the life of this world deceive you, nor let the Chief Deceiver¬†deceive you about Allah"
  35,6,"Surely Satan is an enemy to you, so take him as an enemy. He only invites his followers to become inmates of the Blaze"
  35,7,Those who disbelieve will have a severe punishment. But those who believe and do good will have forgiveness and a great reward
  35,8,"Are those whose evil-doing is made so appealing to them that they deem it good ňĻlike those who are rightly guidedňļ? ňĻIt isňļ certainly Allah ňĻWhoňļ leaves to stray whoever He wills, and guides whoever He wills. So do not grieve yourself to death over them ňĻO Prophetňļ. Surely Allah is All-Knowing of what they do"
  35,9,"And it is Allah Who sends the winds, which then stir up ňĻvapour, formingňļ clouds, and then We drive them to a lifeless land, giving life to the earth after its death. Similar is the Resurrection"
  35,10,"Whoever seeks honour and power, then ňĻlet them know thatňļ all honour and power belongs to Allah. To Him ňĻaloneňļ good words ascend, and righteous deeds are raised up by Him. As for those who plot evil, they will suffer a severe punishment. And the plotting of such ňĻpeopleňļ is doomed ňĻto failňļ"
  35,11,"And ňĻit isňļ Allah ňĻWhoňļ created you from dust,¬†then ňĻdeveloped youňļ from a sperm-drop, then made you into pairs.¬†No female ever conceives or delivers without His knowledge. And no one‚Äôs life is made long or cut short but is ňĻwrittenňļ in a Record.¬†That is certainly easy for Allah"
  35,12,"The two bodies of water are not alike: one is fresh, palatable, and pleasant to drink and the other is salty and bitter. Yet from them both you eat tender seafood and extract ornaments to wear. And you see the ships ploughing their way through both, so you may seek His bounty and give thanks ňĻto Himňļ"
  35,13,"He merges the night into the day and the day into the night, and has subjected the sun and the moon, each orbiting for an appointed term. That is Allah‚ÄĒyour Lord! All authority belongs to Him. But those ňĻidolsňļ you invoke besides Him do not possess even the skin of a date stone"
  35,14,"If you call upon them, they cannot hear your calls. And if they were to hear, they could not respond to you. On the Day of Judgment they will disown your worship ňĻof themňļ. And no one can inform you ňĻO Prophetňļ like the All-Knowledgeable"
  35,15,"O humanity! It is you who stand in need of Allah, but Allah ňĻaloneňļ is the Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  35,16,"If He willed, He could eliminate you and produce a new creation"
  35,17,And that is not difficult for Allah ňĻat allňļ
  35,18,"No soul burdened with sin will bear the burden of another. And if a sin-burdened soul cries for help with its burden, none of it will be carried‚ÄĒeven by a close relative. You ňĻO Prophetňļ can only warn those who stand in awe of their Lord without seeing Him¬†and establish prayer. Whoever purifies themselves, they only do so for their own good. And to Allah is the final return"
  35,19,Those blind ňĻto the truthňļ and those who can see are not equal
  35,20,nor are the darkness and the light
  35,21,nor the ňĻscorchingňļ heat and the ňĻcoolňļ shade
  35,22,"Nor are the dead and the living equal. Indeed, Allah ňĻaloneňļ makes whoever He wills hear, but you ňĻO Prophetňļ can never make those in the graves hear ňĻyour callňļ"
  35,23,You are only a warner
  35,24,We have surely sent you with the truth as a deliverer of good news and a warner. There is no community that has not had a warner
  35,25,"If they deny you, so did those before them. Their messengers came to them with clear proofs, divine Books, and enlightening Scriptures"
  35,26,Then I seized those who persisted in disbelief. How severe was My response
  35,27,"Do you not see that Allah sends down rain from the sky with which We bring forth fruits of different colours? And in the mountains are streaks of varying shades of white, red, and raven black"
  35,28,"just as people, living beings, and cattle are of various colours as well. Of all of Allah‚Äôs servants, only the knowledgeable ňĻof His mightňļ are ňĻtrulyňļ in awe of Him. Allah is indeed Almighty, All-Forgiving"
  35,29,"Surely those who recite the Book of Allah, establish prayer, and donate from what We have provided for them‚ÄĒsecretly and openly‚ÄĒňĻcanňļ hope for an exchange that will never fail"
  35,30,"so that He will reward them in full and increase them out of His grace. He is truly All-Forgiving, Most Appreciative"
  35,31,"The Book We have revealed to you ňĻO Prophetňļ is the truth, confirming what came before it.¬†Surely Allah is All-Aware, All-Seeing of His servants"
  35,32,"Then We granted the Book to those We have chosen from Our servants. Some of them wrong themselves, some follow a middle course, and some are foremost in good deeds by Allah‚Äôs Will. That is ňĻtrulyňļ the greatest bounty"
  35,33,"They will enter the Gardens of Eternity, where they will be adorned with bracelets of gold and pearls, and their clothing will be silk"
  35,34,"And they will say, ‚ÄúPraise be to Allah, Who has kept away from us all ňĻcauses ofňļ sorrow. Our Lord is indeed All-Forgiving, Most Appreciative"
  35,35,"ňĻHe is the Oneňļ Who‚ÄĒout of His grace‚ÄĒhas settled us in the Home of Everlasting Stay, where we will be touched by neither fatigue nor weariness.‚ÄĚ"
  35,36,"As for the disbelievers, they will have the Fire of Hell, where they will not be ňĻallowed to beňļ finished by death, nor will its torment be lightened for them. This is how We reward every ňĻstubbornňļ disbeliever"
  35,37,"There they will be ňĻferventlyňļ screaming, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Take us out ňĻand send us backňļ. We will do good, unlike what we used to do.‚ÄĚ ňĻThey will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúDid We not give you lives long enough so that whoever wanted to be mindful could have done so? And the warner came to you. So taste ňĻthe punishmentňļ, for the wrongdoers have no helper.‚ÄĚ"
  35,38,"Indeed, Allah is the Knower of the unseen of the heavens and the earth. He surely knows best what is ňĻhiddenňļ in the heart"
  35,39,"He is the One Who has placed you as successors on earth. So whoever disbelieves will bear ňĻthe burden ofňļ their own disbelief. The disbelievers‚Äô denial only increases them in contempt in the sight of their Lord, and it will only contribute to their loss"
  35,40,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúHave you considered your associate-gods which you invoke besides Allah? Show me what they have created on earth! Or do they have a share in ňĻthe creation ofňļ the heavens? Or have We given the polytheists a Book, which serves as a clear proof for them? In fact, the wrongdoers promise each other nothing but delusion.‚ÄĚ"
  35,41,"Indeed, Allah ňĻaloneňļ keeps the heavens and the earth from falling apart. If they were to fall apart, none but Him could hold them up. He is truly Most Forbearing, All-Forgiving"
  35,42,"They swore by Allah their most solemn oaths that if a warner were to come to them, they would certainly be better guided than any other community. Yet when a warner did come to them, it only drove them farther away‚ÄĒ"
  35,43,"behaving arrogantly in the land and plotting evil. But evil plotting only backfires on those who plot. Are they awaiting anything but the fate of those ňĻdestroyedňļ before? You will find no change in the way of Allah, nor will you find it diverted ňĻto someone elseňļ"
  35,44,"Have they not travelled throughout the land to see what was the end of those ňĻdestroyedňļ before them? They were far superior in might. But there is nothing that can escape Allah in the heavens or the earth. He is certainly All-Knowing, Most Capable"
  35,45,"If Allah were to punish people ňĻimmediatelyňļ for what they have committed, He would not have left a single living being on earth. But He delays them for an appointed term. And when their time arrives, then surely Allah is All-Seeing of His servants"
