  36,18,"The people replied, ‚ÄúWe definitely see you as a bad omen for us. If you do not desist, we will certainly stone you ňĻto deathňļ and you will be touched with a painful punishment from us.‚ÄĚ"
  36,19,"The messengers said, ‚ÄúYour bad omen lies within yourselves. Are you saying this because you are reminded ňĻof the truthňļ? In fact, you are a transgressing people.‚ÄĚ"
  36,20,"Then from the farthest end of the city a man came, rushing. He advised, ‚ÄúO my people! Follow the messengers"
